@node "system" "System requirements"
@next "installation"
@prev "legal"
TinyPlayer needs version 36 or newer of the Kickstart. It also needs
ptreplay.library V4 to play ProTracker modules. medplayer.library V5 and
octaplayer.library V5 are required to play MED-modules. These three
libraries are included in this archive.

xpkmaster.library must be available to load files packed with XPK.
powerpacker.library is required to load powerpacked files.
asl.library V36 is used for filerequesters.
@endnode

@node "installation" "Installation"
@next "usage"
@prev "system"
There is no Installer script for TinyPlayer. You have to install it
manually.

First copy the libraries to your LIBS: directory. Then I suggest that you
rename the executable file as TP and copy it, together with it's icon, to a
directory in your path. The ARexx file should be copied to REXX:.
@endnode

@node "usage" "Usage"
@next "bugs"
@prev "installation"
TinyPlayer can used both from @{"CLI" link "cli_usage" 0} and from @{"Workbench" link "wb_usage" 0}. It also has an
@{"ARexx interface" link "arexx_usage" 0}.

TinyPlayer will open a small window on a public screen of your choice. To
stop playing the module and quit the program, just click on the close
gadget of the window. Other ways to quit TinyPlayer is through the ARexx
interface or by sending CTRL-C to the process.

TinyPlayer is pure and can be made resident. I can't see the point of
running it more than once at the same time, though. :-)

 @{"CLI" link "cli_usage" 0}

 @{"Workbench" link "wb_usage" 0}

 @{"ARexx" link "arexx_usage" 0}
@endnode

@node "bugs" "Known bugs"
@next "author"
@prev "usage"
If you first play a PT module and then a MED or OctaMED module TinyPlayer
will report "Could not allocate resources needed to play module". This is
actually not a bug. It happens because ptreplay.library V5 does not release
the audio channels unless it is flushed out of memory. This means that a
simple AVAIL FLUSH will solve the problem in most cases.

This problem should not occur if you use ptreplay.library V6. However V6.3
has a severe bug. It is therefore not distributed with TinyPlayer.
ptreplay.library V6.4 will probably solve all problems.
@endnode

